santi Inspiration Award Transfer FAQs UNT's Academic Standards UNT » Colleges & Schools » CAS » Advising » Scholarships The College of Arts and Sciences offers scholarships and other forms of support to both undergraduate and graduate students. Some of these opportunities, administered by the Dean's Office are college wide. In many instances, students also need to complete application materials on the UNT Student Financial Aid & Scholarships web site. Online Scholarship application Please read eligibility and submission requirements for each scholarship on the menu to the left.  NOTE: Award amounts vary based on available funding. Departmental Scholarships available below. Dean's List Scholarship An endowment fund to supporting undergraduate students enrolled in a degree program within the College of Arts and Sciences who have demonstrated academic promise. Applications are available starting August through February. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. Dean’s Graduate Scholarship An endowment fund to supporting graduate students enrolled in a degree program within the College of Arts and Sciences who have demonstrated academic promise. Applications are available starting August through February. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. Robert J. Hardin Scholarship in Arts & Sciences An endowment fund supporting a scholarship supporting undergraduate and graduate students enrolled in a degree program within the College of Arts & Sciences who have demonstrated academic promise. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. The Charles T. and Mildred L. Newell Memorial Scholarship A scholarship supporting undergraduate students enrolled in a degree program within the College of Arts and Sciences who have demonstrated academic promise. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. The John A. Altermann and Katherine M. Bradford Scholarship A scholarship supporting graduate students in Sciences and Mathematics. It is awarded to a graduate student in either Biology, Chemistry, Math or Physics, rotating the departments every four years beginning with Chemistry in 2008. To learn more about applying for this scholarship, please inquire to the appropriate department and read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. Frank C. Spencer Rural Student Scholarship A scholarship supporting recent high school graduate students enrolling in a degree program within the College of Arts and Sciences who have demonstrated academic promise. Applications are available starting August through February. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. The Voertman-Ardoin Memorial Scholarship A fund supporting students enrolled in a degree program within the College of Arts and Sciences; preference given to students enrolled in English or Philosophy and to first generation students. Applications are available starting August through February. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. AM Willis Endowed Scholarship An endowment fund supporting a scholarship supporting undergraduate and graduate students enrolled in a degree program within the College of Arts & Sciences who have demonstrated academic promise. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. Robert H & Jimmie G. Nobles Scholarship A scholarship supporting graduate and undergraduate students enrolled in a degree program within the College of Arts and Sciences who have demonstrated academic promise. To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirements on the menu to the left. The Aspiring Actuary Scholarship A scholarship supporting undergraduate students in Mathematics seeking the Undergraduate Academic Certificate in Actuarial Science.  To learn more please read eligibility and submission requirement on the menu to the left. College of Arts and Sciences Department/Program Scholarships Aerospace Studies http://www.afrotc.com/scholarships/ Army ROTC http://armyrotc.unt.edu/about-us Biological Sciences http://biology.unt.edu/undergraduate-programs/financial-support-undergraduates Chemistry http://chemistry.unt.edu/undergraduate-program/chemistry-majors-scholarships-awards Communication Studies http://communication.unt.edu/undergraduate-program/scholarships-financial-aid-information Dance and Theatre http://www.danceandtheatre.unt.edu/current-students/financial-aid-scholarships Economics http://economics.unt.edu/undergraduate/undergraduate-scholarships English http://english.unt.edu/undergraduate/undergraduate-scholarships Geography http://geography.unt.edu/academic-programs/grant-scholarship-and-fellowship-opportunities History http://history.unt.edu/undergraduate-program Institute of Applied Sciences http://ias.unt.edu International Studies http://internationalstudies.unt.edu/resources/scholarships Jewish Studies http://jewishstudies.unt.edu/scholarships Journalism http://journalism.unt.edu/undergraduate/scholarships Mathematics http://math.unt.edu/courses-and-schedules/undergraduate-program/undergraduate-program-financial-assistance Philosophy & Religion Studies http://philosophy.unt.edu/scholarships Physics http://physics.unt.edu/undergraduate-studies/scholarship-opportunities Political Science http://politicalscience.unt.edu/undergraduate/scholarships Psychology http://psychology.unt.edu/undergraduate-program/undergraduate-awards Radio, Television, & Film http://mediaarts.unt.edu/undergraduate-studies/scholarships Sociology http://sociology.unt.edu/undergraduate/scholarships Teach North Texas http://teachnorthtexas.unt.edu/resources/scholarships-grants   Technical Communications https://techcomm.unt.edu/node/4420 Women's Studies http://womensstudies.unt.edu/undergraduate-studies/undergraduate-s